WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:34.559 --> 00:36.754
''From Arthur Kahn to Tom Sanders.

00:37.662 --> 00:40.392
''Product Name: Arcamax CD-ROM.

00:40.665 --> 00:44.328
''Considering the merger, I thought
you should get this at home:

00:44.502 --> 00:48.836
''Arcamax production lines running
at 29% despite all efforts.

00:49.174 --> 00:51.904
''Spot-checks on dada dada....

00:52.410 --> 00:55.902
''Speaking of the merger, are
you rich and famous yet?

00:56.081 --> 00:59.073
''Congratulations in
advance on your promotion.

00:59.351 --> 01:00.511
''Arthur.''

01:04.355 --> 01:06.586
Dad, you got E-mail.

01:07.859 --> 01:10.794
I'm not a pain in the ass,
I'm being a lawyer.

01:10.929 --> 01:12.590
There's a difference.

01:12.797 --> 01:16.858
No more computer games, Matt, it's time
for school. Eliza, where are you?

01:17.035 --> 01:18.866
You got E-mail.

01:19.037 --> 01:21.801
Tom, Matt's got toothpaste
all over himself!

01:23.875 --> 01:27.811
If you can't get them ready for
school, don't say you'll do it.

01:27.946 --> 01:29.038
You're welcome.

01:29.214 --> 01:30.442
I'm here.

01:30.615 --> 01:33.106
-And Liza needs a jacket.
-I know she needs a jacket!

01:33.318 --> 01:35.377
A jacket doesn't go, dad.

01:35.954 --> 01:37.182
Wear a sweatshirt.

01:37.422 --> 01:39.390
That's for girls, a white sweatshirt.

01:39.557 --> 01:40.888
Since when?

01:41.459 --> 01:43.393
Leave me alone.

01:47.832 --> 01:49.891
Put your jacket on.

01:50.068 --> 01:53.469
Ariel doesn't have a father.
She has two mothers.

01:53.638 --> 01:55.128
That's interesting.

01:55.340 --> 01:58.969
He's in a hotel with his secretary
patched in from New York...

01:59.144 --> 02:02.079
...while I'm brushing Cheerios
from my file folders.

02:02.247 --> 02:03.339
It's insanity.

02:03.481 --> 02:04.971
Put your jacket on.

02:05.150 --> 02:06.913
Put this on, sweetie.

02:07.085 --> 02:09.076
You can take it off at school.

02:09.253 --> 02:11.245
Listen to your mom.

02:11.423 --> 02:13.357
Matt, did you pee?

02:13.491 --> 02:17.928
I don't know why you said you'd
help me today, with your promotion.

02:18.096 --> 02:19.996
What's dad got around his neck?

02:20.165 --> 02:21.928
You don't know what this is?

02:22.267 --> 02:23.495
It's a tie.

02:23.668 --> 02:25.101
Dad's getting a promotion.

02:25.270 --> 02:27.101
-Dad, you got an E-mail.
-Thanks, honey. Let's go.

02:27.505 --> 02:28.597
We're late.

02:35.180 --> 02:37.444
Did you get the Disneyland tickets?

02:37.615 --> 02:39.606
With everything I have to do?

02:39.784 --> 02:41.615
It's just one call.

02:41.786 --> 02:42.878
Who are they for?

02:43.021 --> 02:46.286
Mohammed Jafar. He's foreman
of the Malaysian plant.

02:46.458 --> 02:49.894
You're the one person I know who
sucks up to the people below you.

02:51.963 --> 02:53.692
Matt, don't kick the seat.

02:53.898 --> 02:55.957
-What's on your tie?
-Toothpaste.

02:56.134 --> 02:59.194
-Let's go.
-Your tie shouldn't look like a bib.

03:23.995 --> 03:25.553
Hi, Cindy, what's up?

03:26.731 --> 03:29.063
Garvin came by the office this morning?

03:29.501 --> 03:30.934
About the promotion?

03:32.237 --> 03:34.068
Matt, will you stop that?

03:35.507 --> 03:38.499
He was surprised I was late?
What does that mean?

03:38.676 --> 03:41.941
Did he say it in passing,
or like he really meant it?

03:47.519 --> 03:50.750
I wonder why Garvin came by
the office at 8 in the morning?

03:50.955 --> 03:52.252
To congratulate you.

03:52.457 --> 03:54.755
He treats everyone like dirt--

03:54.959 --> 03:56.950
Except the top guys.

04:00.765 --> 04:02.596
Except the top guys.

04:03.601 --> 04:06.764
When this merger with
Conley-White goes through...

04:06.971 --> 04:09.201
...and they spin off our division...

04:09.374 --> 04:11.035
...we're going to be rich.

04:11.209 --> 04:12.608
We're already rich.

04:12.777 --> 04:14.039
No, I mean...

04:14.279 --> 04:15.871
...really rich.

04:16.481 --> 04:18.779
My grandmother used to say:

04:18.983 --> 04:22.544
''Don't climb up there too close
to God, He might shake the tree.''

04:34.732 --> 04:36.063
Tom!

04:36.634 --> 04:38.295
Thanks for this morning.

05:05.096 --> 05:07.030
Smaller, faster, cheaper, better.

05:08.032 --> 05:10.262
Remember
lugging the first ones around?

05:10.535 --> 05:14.164
People were amazed. It was like
showing a Polaroid to a bushman.

05:14.339 --> 05:17.433
Now, if it's bigger than a credit
card, it's too inconvenient.

05:17.609 --> 05:19.099
Keeps you on your toes.

05:19.277 --> 05:21.837
Eddie, it's Tom. Cindy said you called.

05:22.180 --> 05:23.545
Sure, I can hold.

05:24.849 --> 05:26.339
How's the job search?

05:27.352 --> 05:30.549
28 years at lBM. Did I
tell you what they told me?

05:30.688 --> 05:33.452
I was ''surplussed.''
Ever hear that word?

05:34.058 --> 05:36.185
What's going on down there?

05:36.794 --> 05:38.455
What? That's crazy.

05:38.630 --> 05:40.461
They should've said, ''sodomized.''

05:40.632 --> 05:45.467
They're not going to sell the
Austin plant. That's just a rumor.

05:45.637 --> 05:49.698
You don't see it coming. You go along,
and then one day there's no room.

05:49.874 --> 05:51.705
No more room for you.

05:52.210 --> 05:53.973
Smaller, faster, cheaper, better.

05:54.145 --> 05:58.878
I won't mention names. I'm just telling
you, it's not true. It's a rumor.

05:59.083 --> 06:01.711
I was making 150 a year. Big money.

06:03.221 --> 06:05.314
It's probably what you make, huh?

06:05.490 --> 06:06.821
Hang on.

06:06.991 --> 06:08.982
Why don't you call Cindy...

06:09.327 --> 06:12.091
...make an appointment.
I'll see if I can help.

06:12.997 --> 06:15.989
Eddie, they are not
going to sell Austin.

06:16.167 --> 06:19.102
If I'm telling you, who else
are you going to believe?

06:19.237 --> 06:19.896
Cindy.

06:20.405 --> 06:21.895
Pretty name.

06:22.240 --> 06:25.607
Used to have fun with the girls.
Nowadays they want your job.

07:06.484 --> 07:07.314
Good morning.

07:07.452 --> 07:10.216
-What did Garvin say? Should I see him?
-He didn't say.

07:10.722 --> 07:11.780
He growled.

07:11.956 --> 07:14.220
He was flirting. Did you get Arthur?

07:14.392 --> 07:16.223
He's standing by on the DVL.

07:16.394 --> 07:18.453
Lunch with Conley-White is at noon.

07:18.663 --> 07:22.292
We'll probably have those
sandwiches with the crusts cut off.

07:22.467 --> 07:24.958
Their jaws were wired shut
at the same prep school.

07:25.169 --> 07:26.966
The merger's still happening?

07:28.072 --> 07:29.061
You heard something?

07:29.574 --> 07:30.404
No.

07:30.575 --> 07:32.167
Just, I....

07:32.477 --> 07:33.967
What's on your tie?

07:34.912 --> 07:36.903
Garvin didn't mention my promotion?

07:37.081 --> 07:38.742
You said you'd be early today.

07:38.916 --> 07:41.316
People from ''Father of the Year''
didn't call?

07:41.753 --> 07:42.811
No.

07:43.254 --> 07:44.687
That's a joke.

07:47.191 --> 07:49.182
5 seconds to Malaysia.

07:49.761 --> 07:50.819
Should I close the door?

07:50.995 --> 07:52.087
Do I ever ask that?

07:52.430 --> 07:53.419
Never.

07:54.599 --> 07:55.998
Malaysian video linkup.

07:58.770 --> 08:00.761
You look good. Awake.

08:00.938 --> 08:02.337
What's wrong with Arcamax?

08:02.507 --> 08:07.001
The drives are very slow. We're
getting seek times in the 140-160 range.

08:07.211 --> 08:10.772
140 isn't a sexy CD player anymore.
Everyone has 140.

08:10.948 --> 08:13.439
My guys think there's a
compatibility problem...

08:13.618 --> 08:16.212
...between the controller chip
and the driver's software.

08:16.354 --> 08:18.288
That'll put us back a year.

08:18.456 --> 08:23.223
The screen flickers. The current cuts
in and out. It's a design problem.

08:23.361 --> 08:26.455
What do you mean?
All laptops have the same design.

08:26.631 --> 08:30.032
I sent you out some drives.
You should get them today.

08:30.234 --> 08:33.294
This is bad, Arthur.
How could this happen?

08:33.471 --> 08:35.631
Going to bury it until the merger?

08:35.807 --> 08:38.799
Don't you say anything.
Does anyone else know?

08:38.976 --> 08:41.967
I'm a grave. What,
are you kidding, Tom?

08:42.145 --> 08:46.139
I still think, really, that
Arcamax will be a major, major hit.

08:46.317 --> 08:48.751
I'll call you when I see the drives.

08:48.886 --> 08:50.547
Did you get the macadamia nuts?

08:50.755 --> 08:52.154
Good night, Arthur.

08:52.490 --> 08:54.151
They are so good.

08:54.325 --> 08:56.759
He's off the phone. I got to go.

08:58.996 --> 09:00.827
Do you know a Meredith Johnson?

09:00.998 --> 09:03.660
-Yes, years ago.
-She wanted to see you.

09:03.835 --> 09:05.166
She's here for the lunch.

09:05.336 --> 09:07.566
The entire company came for this lunch?

09:07.772 --> 09:10.070
Garvin brought up the Operations Group.

09:10.408 --> 09:12.273
Meredith is in Operations?

09:12.410 --> 09:15.573
What should I tell her?
Bad day, in-laws in town?

09:15.780 --> 09:18.772
I'm going to see Lewyn about
the 900s. Stop worrying.

09:18.916 --> 09:22.579
If there was bad news Garvin
would've sent Phil Blackburn.

09:28.826 --> 09:29.656
Phil.

09:30.862 --> 09:32.921
Are you coming to see me?

09:33.364 --> 09:34.922
No. Why?

09:35.099 --> 09:36.794
Nothing. How are you?

09:36.934 --> 09:40.028
How are you, Tom?
You look all beat up.

09:40.204 --> 09:41.193
I do?

09:41.372 --> 09:45.103
You're letting it get to you.
Don't take it personally.

09:45.309 --> 09:46.867
Take what personally?

09:47.044 --> 09:49.035
Maybe it's just a rumor.

09:49.213 --> 09:50.441
What's a rumor?

09:50.615 --> 09:54.051
I don't want to spread rumors.
That's how these things get started.

09:54.218 --> 09:55.207
You mean Austin?

09:55.386 --> 09:56.375
Who said that?

09:56.554 --> 09:57.612
What am I missing?

09:58.222 --> 10:01.055
I can't believe he didn't tell you.
He's so perverse.

10:01.225 --> 10:02.192
Tell me what?

10:03.628 --> 10:05.220
So, how's Susan?

10:06.130 --> 10:07.620
Susan's good.

10:07.832 --> 10:09.322
-How's Lonnie?
-Great.

10:11.569 --> 10:14.834
-Did you know she got tenure?
-That's great.

10:17.909 --> 10:19.968
Here's my stop.

10:23.247 --> 10:25.238
I tried to explain to Garvin.

10:25.583 --> 10:27.642
You know him, he's like a child.

10:27.852 --> 10:31.413
Fuck your feelings if they
interfere with his surprise.

10:31.589 --> 10:35.081
-What surprise?
-Rumor is you're getting passed over.

10:37.094 --> 10:38.527
So I'm not getting the VP job?

10:38.596 --> 10:39.654
That's the rumor.

10:39.864 --> 10:41.855
Rumors are always true.

10:41.999 --> 10:43.364
Garvin didn't say anything?

10:43.501 --> 10:46.493
Came by the office. I was late,
Susan had a conference.

10:46.671 --> 10:49.105
-You were late? Today?
-Why're you in Seattle?

10:49.273 --> 10:50.865
Good to see you again.

10:56.881 --> 11:01.614
Somebody tells Garvin I was talking to
you.... You know how he is about leaks.

11:01.886 --> 11:04.116
Leak? I thought it was a rumor.

11:04.288 --> 11:07.951
It was different before.
I could watch your back.

11:08.125 --> 11:10.525
Who gets the job, Stephanie Kaplan?

11:10.695 --> 11:12.890
Rumor is he went outside the group.

11:13.030 --> 11:15.624
You'd still head up Manufacturing...

11:15.800 --> 11:17.028
...presumably.

11:19.704 --> 11:20.796
Wait a minute.

11:22.206 --> 11:23.901
I might be out of a job?

11:24.141 --> 11:25.631
Don't get paranoid.

11:25.810 --> 11:26.970
I'm a quick learner.

11:27.144 --> 11:31.308
You wouldn't make someone VP and
not let them appoint their own team.

11:31.482 --> 11:33.211
How would that look?

11:34.151 --> 11:36.051
Am I out of a job?

11:36.988 --> 11:38.649
Come on, Tom.

11:38.990 --> 11:40.821
I'm already out on a limb.

11:51.068 --> 11:53.434
Are you okay? You want a Prozac?

11:53.571 --> 11:55.664
No, I'm fine.

11:56.073 --> 11:58.667
I'm disappointed, but I'm fine.

12:04.448 --> 12:05.506
You sure?

12:06.350 --> 12:10.013
Don't worry about me. I'm a
stockholder. Whatever's...

12:10.187 --> 12:11.745
...best for the company...

12:34.045 --> 12:38.209
Leave a message for Susan, Tom,
Matt and Eliza, after the beep.

12:38.382 --> 12:40.043
Thanks for calling. Bye.

12:46.490 --> 12:49.288
-Obviously, he's disappointed.
-But he took it well?

12:49.493 --> 12:51.620
Overall, I'd say yes.

12:51.796 --> 12:55.232
No bumps before the merger.
I don't want him quitting.

12:55.399 --> 12:56.889
It's up to you.

12:57.068 --> 12:59.502
Just one big happy family.

12:59.637 --> 13:00.899
You got that?

13:01.238 --> 13:06.141
I have to say, going down to see
him this morning was a masterstroke.

13:06.510 --> 13:08.808
It really put him on the defensive.

13:09.013 --> 13:10.742
I'll keep an eye on him.

13:10.915 --> 13:12.644
He'll get on the program.

13:12.817 --> 13:15.581
When push comes to shove,
he has no guts.

13:23.594 --> 13:26.324
Let me ask you something.
You know Susan.

13:27.765 --> 13:29.528
If I heard a rumor about the...

13:29.667 --> 13:31.658
...future of the company...

13:32.436 --> 13:33.664
...my future...

13:34.038 --> 13:36.768
...you know, nothing crazy,
a real rumor...

13:37.541 --> 13:41.102
...what would Susan say?
You think she'd say to see Garvin?

14:00.197 --> 14:01.789
Here's someone you should meet.

14:02.066 --> 14:04.364
Tom Sanders. He heads up Manufacturing.

14:04.568 --> 14:07.128
Steven Chase, Crescent Capital.
John Conley.

14:07.304 --> 14:08.464
You're John Conley?

14:08.806 --> 14:12.367
Junior. Dad's coming on Friday
with members of the Board.

14:12.710 --> 14:15.474
-Catch you at the lunch.
-Tom, come in.

14:16.714 --> 14:18.375
You wanted to see me.

14:18.582 --> 14:21.642
Yeah, sorry about this morning.
You know how kids are.

14:21.819 --> 14:24.310
Have you met Meredith Johnson?

14:25.156 --> 14:27.716
What's wrong? That's a
hello you'd give to a rash.

14:27.892 --> 14:30.156
I'm preoccupied. It's not you.

14:30.327 --> 14:32.659
We go way back. He broke my heart.

14:32.830 --> 14:34.388
She's making that up.

14:34.598 --> 14:37.226
I thought your heart
was made of plastic.

14:37.401 --> 14:39.232
He said I could be anything I wanted.

14:39.403 --> 14:41.394
-He was right.
-It was a line.

14:41.605 --> 14:44.005
-It wasn't a line.
-I didn't know you were acquainted.

14:44.175 --> 14:47.838
Wilde said, ''I like a man with a
future and a woman with a past.''

14:48.012 --> 14:49.673
I heard you were in Operations.

14:50.748 --> 14:53.012
I don't know. Am I?

14:54.351 --> 14:58.617
The last few years I've been cleaning
up the mess Bob made of this company.

14:59.123 --> 15:01.523
If it's such a mess, why am I so rich?

15:01.692 --> 15:03.683
Yes, but you're a lot richer now.

15:03.861 --> 15:05.852
We should catch up. Get together.

15:06.030 --> 15:07.122
I'd love that.

15:07.264 --> 15:08.925
Plenty of time now.

15:09.366 --> 15:12.529
Flying over Wyoming, I
thought the merger was dead.

15:12.703 --> 15:17.265
Conley was choking on the valuation.
The spin-off was Meredith's idea.

15:17.441 --> 15:19.932
Conley thinks it was their idea.

15:20.211 --> 15:22.941
-Really?
-Lit them up like a Christmas tree.

15:23.147 --> 15:24.375
She saved the merger.

15:24.648 --> 15:27.640
You have money now.
You can even buy a new tie.

15:30.721 --> 15:33.884
So, what was it you
wanted to see me about?

15:36.360 --> 15:40.160
Meredith-fucking-Johnson!
Son-of-a-bitch. Goddamn Garvin.

15:40.331 --> 15:41.355
-What happened?
-I didn't get it.

15:41.532 --> 15:43.591
-You're not the new VP?
-He announced it?

15:43.767 --> 15:46.702
It was a secret. He's got
her installed in the office...

15:46.871 --> 15:48.862
...bouncing quips back and forth.

15:49.039 --> 15:49.869
Who?

15:50.040 --> 15:52.440
-Who's she?
-Will this affect the spin-off?

15:52.610 --> 15:56.376
She doesn't know the difference
between software and a sweater.

15:56.547 --> 15:58.037
What aren't you telling us?

15:58.215 --> 16:02.276
I might be out of a job.
You know what it's like out there?

16:02.453 --> 16:03.943
What about the spin-off?

16:04.121 --> 16:08.387
They didn't tell me about me!
Would they tell me about the spin-off?!

16:10.895 --> 16:12.385
I'm sorry.

16:13.631 --> 16:16.464
This is the worst day of my life.
All right?

16:17.234 --> 16:18.394
Who is she?

16:18.569 --> 16:20.400
Let me guess: attractive?

16:20.638 --> 16:22.071
What does that matter?

16:22.239 --> 16:24.139
Nipples like pencil erasers?

16:24.308 --> 16:26.469
She's attractive. Very attractive.

16:26.644 --> 16:27.906
Sleeping with Garvin?

16:28.078 --> 16:29.807
That's why he got a Nordic Track.

16:29.980 --> 16:32.642
It's a curse to be me.
Life holds no surprises.

16:32.816 --> 16:34.647
This is such a cliche.

16:34.919 --> 16:37.479
How do you think a
cliche becomes a cliche?

16:37.655 --> 16:39.748
You mean like, ''Size doesn't matter''?

16:40.758 --> 16:42.419
I have a thing for you.

16:42.593 --> 16:45.585
All right, please, can
we get some work done?

16:45.763 --> 16:48.254
We got a small problem with Arcamax.

16:48.432 --> 16:50.332
-It's not the design.
-It's not the code.

16:50.501 --> 16:54.938
Any woman must be twice as good as
a man and work harder for less pay.

16:55.105 --> 16:56.936
Cliche grande.

16:57.107 --> 16:59.007
How does a cliche become one?

16:59.176 --> 17:02.612
It is very weird. We know
nothing about this woman.

17:02.780 --> 17:03.610
I do.

17:03.847 --> 17:05.508
I had a thing with her.

17:06.450 --> 17:07.781
You are amazing.

17:08.452 --> 17:09.942
It was years ago.

17:10.354 --> 17:12.617
You've seen more ass than a rental car.

17:12.856 --> 17:16.019
Get a few more women in your
life so you can be a census.

17:16.359 --> 17:18.123
Maybe you can sleep your way up.

17:18.462 --> 17:19.451
Right.

17:19.630 --> 17:22.690
Wait, why? Why her and not Tom?
He's not attractive?

17:22.866 --> 17:24.696
Men and women are different.

17:24.867 --> 17:26.460
Not in a way that matters to you.

17:27.471 --> 17:29.029
Are you saying I'm a virgin?

17:41.352 --> 17:44.082
Meanwhile, you were asking
me about the spin-off.

17:44.588 --> 17:46.681
Garvin said it was her idea.

17:53.931 --> 17:56.593
It's always such a
pleasure to come here...

17:56.800 --> 17:59.291
...and be with the
Advanced Products Group.

17:59.436 --> 18:02.200
I feel such a warmth
for the people here.

18:02.373 --> 18:06.207
I feel a kinship. And I've
always wanted to give you...

18:06.377 --> 18:07.867
Is this seat taken?

18:08.712 --> 18:12.204
...the most advanced original
leadership that I could.

18:12.383 --> 18:13.816
How are you?

18:13.951 --> 18:17.614
-Sorry you didn't get the promotion.
-I'm sorry you didn't get it either.

18:18.889 --> 18:20.220
How long have you known?

18:22.626 --> 18:24.218
Really? That long?

18:24.628 --> 18:27.392
Every time I've wanted
to promote a woman...

18:27.564 --> 18:29.464
...to break the glass ceiling...

18:29.633 --> 18:31.828
...it's always the same story:

18:31.969 --> 18:34.233
''But, Bob.... But, Bob....''

18:35.139 --> 18:40.076
I've thought about it often since my
daughter's death, that had she lived...

18:40.244 --> 18:42.474
...it would be extremely rare...

18:42.646 --> 18:44.910
...that she ever got to run a company.

18:46.083 --> 18:48.847
So it has a special meaning
for me when I tell you...

