01:36:16.028 --> 01:36:17.017
Friends?

01:36:19.865 --> 01:36:20.763
What?

01:36:21.100 --> 01:36:24.263
I hope you still think
of me as a friend.

01:36:26.105 --> 01:36:27.436
Good night, Phil.

01:36:31.043 --> 01:36:33.273
Sign it now and I'll read it later.

01:36:34.046 --> 01:36:35.377
Where will you be?

01:36:35.548 --> 01:36:38.039
Here, working on the presentation.

01:36:38.217 --> 01:36:41.709
If not, I'll have somebody
run this by your house later.

01:36:49.295 --> 01:36:51.058
Let me ask you something.

01:36:51.797 --> 01:36:53.287
Why'd she do this?

01:36:53.733 --> 01:36:57.635
You've seen her in action.
She's cool, smart and in control.

01:36:57.803 --> 01:37:01.068
-How'd she lose control like this?
-I don't know.

01:37:01.307 --> 01:37:03.400
You're attractive. Maybe.

01:37:03.576 --> 01:37:07.478
-But not irresistible.
-I'm serious. She's here one day.

01:37:07.646 --> 01:37:10.740
There's a merger going on.
Conley people are touchy.

01:37:10.916 --> 01:37:12.474
She thought you'd go along.

01:37:12.651 --> 01:37:14.642
-There's more to it than that.
-Come on.

01:37:14.820 --> 01:37:17.653
You think too much.
You need to go home...

01:37:17.823 --> 01:37:20.257
...open a nice bottle of champagne...

01:37:20.426 --> 01:37:23.589
...make up with your
wife and get some sleep.

01:37:23.763 --> 01:37:25.162
It's over.

01:37:27.800 --> 01:37:29.062
Thank you.

01:37:29.201 --> 01:37:31.567
Absolutely. You're welcome.

01:37:32.138 --> 01:37:33.298
Good night.

01:37:33.472 --> 01:37:34.564
Good night.

01:38:04.003 --> 01:38:05.231
Hi, Stephanie.

01:38:05.404 --> 01:38:09.238
Must be difficult, nobody
giving you information.

01:38:09.408 --> 01:38:10.841
It's been a crazy week.

01:38:11.410 --> 01:38:15.403
I had a friend. She was one of
the first women to move high up.

01:38:15.748 --> 01:38:19.343
You know what it's like,
every day putting out fires.

01:38:19.618 --> 01:38:22.246
It turned out the job
wasn't what she thought.

01:38:22.421 --> 01:38:25.254
She was looking the wrong
way when they fired her.

01:38:26.125 --> 01:38:27.422
lnteresting.

01:38:27.693 --> 01:38:30.685
Truth usually is, once you get to it.

01:38:48.647 --> 01:38:49.944
It's you.

01:38:50.282 --> 01:38:51.271
Where is everyone?

01:38:51.450 --> 01:38:55.216
Mr. Garvin came in an hour ago.
Said they were working too hard.

01:38:55.387 --> 01:38:56.877
Sent everyone home.

01:39:57.516 --> 01:40:00.007
-What if Sanders doesn't bring it up?
-He will.

01:40:00.219 --> 01:40:03.211
I talked to him about his
presentation on Arcamax.

01:40:03.355 --> 01:40:04.845
He has no idea.

01:40:05.024 --> 01:40:06.719
When he brings up the line....

01:40:06.859 --> 01:40:09.623
You must pounce because we
don't have the harassment.

01:40:09.795 --> 01:40:12.787
It must be that Sanders
is incompetent.

01:40:14.033 --> 01:40:16.627
It'll be in public. With reporters.

01:40:16.969 --> 01:40:18.732
Bob's counting on you.

01:40:19.038 --> 01:40:21.370
Let's clean out the database.

01:40:21.540 --> 01:40:22.871
And any backup.

01:40:28.881 --> 01:40:31.543
Catherine,
can you hold on one minute?

01:40:38.157 --> 01:40:40.751
Has my contract gone out already?

01:40:40.893 --> 01:40:42.258
Shit.

01:40:42.828 --> 01:40:45.319
What does it say about firing me?

01:40:45.497 --> 01:40:48.557
They can fire me for cause,
can't they? For incompetence?

01:40:49.501 --> 01:40:53.562
The problem with the drives is not
with the programming or the design.

01:40:53.772 --> 01:40:57.401
It's with the production line
and that's my responsibility.

01:40:57.843 --> 01:40:59.572
This whole thing tomorrow...

01:40:59.912 --> 01:41:01.777
...they're setting me up.

01:42:12.751 --> 01:42:14.742
Housekeeping, please.

01:42:16.355 --> 01:42:18.255
This is Mr. Conley.

01:42:18.424 --> 01:42:21.086
Could someone come
and turn down my bed?

01:42:21.593 --> 01:42:25.256
My room number? It's on
the phone here somewhere....

01:42:26.665 --> 01:42:27.859
That's right.

01:42:28.000 --> 01:42:29.763
Thank you very much.

01:42:36.508 --> 01:42:40.774
-When does your dad arrive?
-Midnight. They stopped in Houston.

01:42:40.946 --> 01:42:43.779
I'd love for him to get a
chance to see the Corridor.

01:42:44.283 --> 01:42:45.375
You know...

01:42:45.784 --> 01:42:50.278
I stayed up late last night, fooling
around with it up in my room.

01:42:50.689 --> 01:42:52.179
It's really incredible.

01:42:58.697 --> 01:43:00.392
I'm sorry, sir.

01:43:00.532 --> 01:43:02.022
Here, thank you.

01:43:02.201 --> 01:43:03.634
-You're welcome.
-Good night.

01:43:03.802 --> 01:43:05.394
Have a nice evening.

01:44:22.981 --> 01:44:27.111
You're in the Corridor, our prototype
for a virtual reality database.

01:44:27.286 --> 01:44:29.277
Enjoy the demonstration.

01:44:29.488 --> 01:44:34.391
lnformation accessed during this demo
is for entertainment value only...

01:44:34.560 --> 01:44:37.723
...and should not be duplicated
to another database.

01:44:37.896 --> 01:44:41.297
If you have any questions,
ask the angel.

01:45:32.851 --> 01:45:35.342
Malaysian Operations.

01:46:14.493 --> 01:46:17.826
Searching Malaysian revisions file.

01:46:18.497 --> 01:46:20.897
Why don't we go up to my suite?

01:46:22.000 --> 01:46:24.992
Give my colleagues a chance
to try out the Corridor.

01:46:25.837 --> 01:46:27.327
Good idea.

01:46:54.533 --> 01:46:57.934
''Reduction of air handling
capacity from number 7 air handlers...

01:46:58.136 --> 01:47:01.128
...to a more appropriate
and cost-effective number 5.''

01:47:01.540 --> 01:47:06.034
You can't put number 5 handlers in
there. You'll have dirt in everything.

01:47:09.214 --> 01:47:11.205
My God, she's in the system.

01:47:29.801 --> 01:47:31.666
Angel, I need help.

01:47:33.905 --> 01:47:35.167
Help is here.

01:47:35.807 --> 01:47:38.571
Can I stop files from being deleted?

01:47:38.744 --> 01:47:40.803
I'm sorry. You're not Level 5.

01:47:45.751 --> 01:47:48.413
You're supposed to protect the files.

01:47:48.587 --> 01:47:51.488
Sysop controls are
restricted to Level 5.

01:48:11.943 --> 01:48:14.434
Show me all communications
with Malaysia.

01:48:14.713 --> 01:48:16.442
Telephone or video?

01:48:16.782 --> 01:48:18.010
Video.

01:48:30.028 --> 01:48:33.964
Show me the last transmission
involving Meredith.

01:48:40.305 --> 01:48:44.298
Sooner or later, Tom will figure
out the changes at the plant.

01:48:44.476 --> 01:48:45.534
He's not stupid.

01:48:45.744 --> 01:48:48.372
Tom will be out of the picture
by Tuesday.

01:48:48.880 --> 01:48:52.816
I don't like to gamble.
I love Tahoe, but I think the risk--

01:48:52.984 --> 01:48:56.545
Think. Who'll believe him?
He's married, with a family.

01:48:56.755 --> 01:48:59.815
He'll have no choice but to
take the settlement and leave.

01:48:59.991 --> 01:49:03.893
Then we say Sanders made the changes
at the plant? He'll deny it.

01:49:04.062 --> 01:49:06.758
He won't know.
He'll be gone by then.

01:49:29.521 --> 01:49:32.183
These things are so darn complicated.

01:49:35.794 --> 01:49:37.284
I think it's upside down.

01:49:49.207 --> 01:49:50.538
There we go.

01:50:02.554 --> 01:50:03.543
Who's first?

01:50:04.122 --> 01:50:06.215
Must have left the system on.

01:50:08.393 --> 01:50:10.623
Give it a try. You'll love it.

01:50:10.829 --> 01:50:12.729
I'd love to try it.

01:50:22.240 --> 01:50:24.333
I am totally screwed.

01:50:25.243 --> 01:50:27.143
I'll make my presentation...

01:50:27.345 --> 01:50:29.905
...Meredith will ask me questions.

01:50:30.081 --> 01:50:32.242
She'll make me
look totally incompetent.

01:50:32.417 --> 01:50:35.250
Are you sure there's not
another system somewhere?

01:50:35.420 --> 01:50:38.082
The system
has been completely deleted.

01:50:38.256 --> 01:50:39.985
So I'm a sitting duck.

01:50:40.492 --> 01:50:44.155
I'll be walking around like
a ghost with a resume.

01:51:08.687 --> 01:51:10.018
It's Mohammed Jafar.

01:51:10.188 --> 01:51:11.519
How are you?

01:51:11.690 --> 01:51:15.285
I don't mean to bug you,
but we're departing Monday--

01:51:15.460 --> 01:51:19.794
It's my fault. Susan got the
Disneyland tickets for you.

01:51:20.031 --> 01:51:21.123
The E-tickets?

01:51:21.299 --> 01:51:25.395
You're comped for all the rides and
at the hotel they'll upgrade you.

01:51:25.537 --> 01:51:28.131
Magnificent. I can't
wait to tell my wife.

01:51:28.306 --> 01:51:31.969
She said you were full of shit.
You know how women are.

01:51:32.143 --> 01:51:34.043
Yes, I sure do.

01:51:34.479 --> 01:51:36.310
I miss your face.

01:51:36.548 --> 01:51:40.541
Talk to Arthur. He sees it
enough on the DVL. I'm always--

01:51:45.924 --> 01:51:47.323
Tom, are you there?

01:51:47.492 --> 01:51:51.929
Mohammed, on this end,
we back up our files on DAT.

01:51:52.063 --> 01:51:54.327
Do you do the same over there?

01:51:54.666 --> 01:51:56.566
I don't know what we have.

01:51:57.335 --> 01:51:59.826
I'd have to check it out. Why?

01:52:00.005 --> 01:52:03.839
I got a real problem here.
I'm up against the wall and...

01:52:04.576 --> 01:52:07.511
...I need you to do some
things for me, Mohammed.

01:52:08.747 --> 01:52:11.011
I hope we have what you need, Tom.

01:52:40.478 --> 01:52:41.604
Daddy?

01:52:42.480 --> 01:52:44.971
I never believed what
they said about you.

01:52:50.488 --> 01:52:51.978
Thank you, honey.

01:52:53.091 --> 01:52:54.991
Come here, big guy.

01:53:03.802 --> 01:53:05.133
Thank you.

01:53:21.653 --> 01:53:23.018
Those from Malaysia?

01:53:23.521 --> 01:53:26.581
I can't believe it's still coming out.
It started at 7.

01:53:48.780 --> 01:53:50.042
Testing.

01:54:08.366 --> 01:54:10.300
Put these in one of the files.

01:54:35.994 --> 01:54:38.656
Yeah, there's a real talent to fishing.

01:54:40.098 --> 01:54:42.589
First you must choose the right bait...

01:54:42.734 --> 01:54:45.225
...then you must know
when to reel it in.

01:54:46.104 --> 01:54:48.504
About the other day, I didn't mean...

01:54:48.673 --> 01:54:49.833
Yes, you did.

01:54:50.608 --> 01:54:52.838
I apologize, and...

01:54:53.011 --> 01:54:54.171
...thank you.

01:54:55.513 --> 01:54:56.844
I accept.

01:55:04.422 --> 01:55:07.118
Which brings us to our
Advanced Products Group.

01:55:07.258 --> 01:55:10.022
Tom Sanders heads our
manufacturing department.

01:55:10.195 --> 01:55:12.026
Tom, can you come up here...

01:55:12.197 --> 01:55:16.361
...and review for us the revolutionary
new product we call Arcamax?

01:55:24.876 --> 01:55:26.639
Thank you, Meredith.

01:55:29.547 --> 01:55:33.449
Arcamax is our own stand-alone
CD-ROM drive player.

01:55:34.052 --> 01:55:37.783
Now, for a CD-ROM drive to be
effective, it must be portable...

01:55:38.056 --> 01:55:39.546
...it has to be fast.

01:55:39.724 --> 01:55:44.457
Arcamax is twice as fast as any
CD-ROM drive in the world today.

01:55:45.063 --> 01:55:48.396
We've had our problems,
but we are solving them.

01:55:48.566 --> 01:55:51.228
And were the problems
with the design?

01:55:51.402 --> 01:55:55.395
No, there are fabrication problems
involving the production line.

01:55:55.573 --> 01:55:56.972
What sort of problems?

01:55:57.675 --> 01:56:01.907
For example, we should be using
automatic chip installers to lock...

01:56:02.080 --> 01:56:03.911
...the control chip on.

01:56:04.082 --> 01:56:06.744
The Malaysians have been
doing it by hand...

01:56:06.918 --> 01:56:09.409
...jamming the chips
in with their thumbs.

01:56:09.587 --> 01:56:12.078
And the quality of the air is dirty.

01:56:12.257 --> 01:56:16.250
We should use level 7 air
handlers, we're using level 5.

01:56:16.427 --> 01:56:19.191
And we're ordering our
components, like...

01:56:19.330 --> 01:56:23.699
...hinge rods and clips, not
from our Singapore supplier...

01:56:23.835 --> 01:56:27.999
...but from someone who's a lot
cheaper but also less reliable.

01:56:28.206 --> 01:56:32.609
I'm confused. You set up this line.
You didn't anticipate these problems?

01:56:33.611 --> 01:56:37.775
The line was changed.
The specifications were altered.

01:56:38.116 --> 01:56:41.517
How is that possible? We know
you to be a competent manager.

01:56:43.521 --> 01:56:47.287
You should know.
You ordered the changes.

01:56:48.293 --> 01:56:50.523
I don't know how you got that idea.

01:56:51.029 --> 01:56:53.293
You were in Kuala Lumpur last year.

01:56:55.033 --> 01:56:59.129
To settle a labor dispute.
I've never even seen the line.

01:57:01.739 --> 01:57:02.967
You haven't?

01:57:03.308 --> 01:57:05.640
No, I don't know who told you I--

01:57:10.448 --> 01:57:12.882
You're watching Malaysian Channel 3.

01:57:19.257 --> 01:57:21.987
Perhaps instead of digging
up Malaysian video clips...

01:57:22.160 --> 01:57:24.651
...we should discuss
the problems here...

01:57:24.829 --> 01:57:27.821
...the problems in your department
with the line you set up.

01:57:28.900 --> 01:57:30.162
All right.

01:57:35.773 --> 01:57:40.506
The 1st memo in the file being handed
out is signed by Meredith Johnson.

01:57:40.678 --> 01:57:44.671
It states that manual labor will
be used to install the chips.

01:57:44.849 --> 01:57:47.409
That made the Malay
government happy.

01:57:47.852 --> 01:57:51.288
It also meant voltage irregularities
and memory allocation--

01:57:51.422 --> 01:57:54.414
The Malay government
insisted we fill those jobs.

01:57:54.592 --> 01:57:58.926
The Malaysian government does
not own shares of DigiCom.

01:57:59.097 --> 01:58:00.928
These people here do.

01:58:02.867 --> 01:58:04.528
The second memo...

01:58:04.702 --> 01:58:08.604
...reduces the air handling
capacity in order to cut costs.

01:58:08.940 --> 01:58:13.877
And that's why we're getting dirt in
the split optics, the drive arms.

01:58:14.112 --> 01:58:19.049
The resulting delays will actually
increase the costs by more than 70%.

01:58:19.317 --> 01:58:23.378
-The third memo regarding--
-The drives are your responsibility!

01:58:24.622 --> 01:58:27.147
These problems were created
because of your incompetence.

01:58:27.759 --> 01:58:29.317
That's what's wrong!

01:58:29.460 --> 01:58:31.451
Passing the buck!
Back stabbing!

01:58:31.629 --> 01:58:32.618
I'm not done.

01:58:32.830 --> 01:58:35.628
This so-called evidence of
yours is fooling no one!

01:58:35.833 --> 01:58:39.894
You can protect your turf
and think it means something.

01:58:40.071 --> 01:58:43.404
You weren't told of these decisions
because they're over your head.

01:58:43.574 --> 01:58:45.906
This merger is about synergy...

01:58:46.077 --> 01:58:49.569
...between hardware and software,
between cash flow and capital needs.

01:58:49.747 --> 01:58:52.079
That's a language
you can't understand!

01:58:52.250 --> 01:58:53.581
I don't either.

01:58:54.419 --> 01:58:57.411
We're buying this company
because they build things.

01:58:58.156 --> 01:59:00.420
You understand what she means?

01:59:07.999 --> 01:59:11.765
I'm trying to convey the
sentiments of everyone here.

01:59:11.936 --> 01:59:13.767
That's what I meant to do.

01:59:18.676 --> 01:59:21.270
Could you step outside
for a moment?

01:59:32.957 --> 01:59:35.289
Can you build the darn thing or not?

01:59:36.194 --> 01:59:37.889
Yes, sir, we can.

01:59:40.698 --> 01:59:44.395
They're replacing Meredith.
Garvin's announcing it in 10 minutes.

01:59:47.305 --> 01:59:48.636
Ten minutes?

02:00:12.563 --> 02:00:14.724
I'm surprised you didn't come to gloat.

02:00:14.932 --> 02:00:19.665
Gloating is underrated. I actually
came here to pick up the Arcamax files.

02:00:19.837 --> 02:00:21.930
Some smart people underrated you.

02:00:22.173 --> 02:00:23.572
Thank you.

02:00:24.242 --> 02:00:25.834
Not including myself.

02:00:26.010 --> 02:00:29.002
I beat you. I beat you fair and square.

02:00:29.514 --> 02:00:31.448
Garvin lost his nerve.

02:00:31.582 --> 02:00:34.847
It was his brilliant idea to
fire you for incompetence.

02:00:35.086 --> 02:00:36.519
Him and Phil.

02:00:36.687 --> 02:00:38.177
Now I'm being fired.

02:00:39.257 --> 02:00:43.751
I've never seen you play the victim.
It's the only good quality you had.

02:00:44.095 --> 02:00:48.259
I'm playing the game men set up,
and I'm being punished for it.

02:00:48.766 --> 02:00:50.199
It's fine.

02:00:50.535 --> 02:00:54.528
I've had calls from ten
head-hunters with job offers.

02:00:55.873 --> 02:00:59.468
Don't be surprised if I'm back
in ten years to buy this place.

02:01:01.546 --> 02:01:06.108
Did it ever occur to you, Meredith,
that maybe I set you up?

02:01:21.566 --> 02:01:24.228
-This is my son, Spencer.
-How you doing?

02:01:24.402 --> 02:01:26.563
-Good.
-You're at the University of Washington?

02:01:26.737 --> 02:01:28.796
That's great. Very good.

02:01:46.090 --> 02:01:47.580
What a week!

02:01:47.758 --> 02:01:49.419
The Chinese say:

02:01:49.927 --> 02:01:53.328
''May you live in interesting times.''

02:01:55.099 --> 02:01:59.433
This merger is the most
interesting merger I've had...

02:01:59.770 --> 02:02:01.328
...since my 2nd marriage.

02:02:02.940 --> 02:02:04.931
The merger is complete.

02:02:05.543 --> 02:02:07.534
The question now is...

02:02:08.179 --> 02:02:12.343
...who do we find to run
things up here in Seattle?

02:02:12.550 --> 02:02:15.041
And what I realized during this...

02:02:15.186 --> 02:02:17.450
...very interesting week...

02:02:17.955 --> 02:02:21.288
...is that I have probably
focused too much on...

02:02:21.459 --> 02:02:25.623
...breaking the glass ceiling,
finding a woman to run things here...

02:02:25.796 --> 02:02:29.562
...when I should have been
looking for the best person...

02:02:29.800 --> 02:02:31.461
...to run things here.

02:02:32.203 --> 02:02:33.568
Someone whose...

02:02:33.704 --> 02:02:38.300
...long service with this company
has established a record...

02:02:38.643 --> 02:02:40.133
...of creativity...

02:02:40.311 --> 02:02:41.972
...sound judgement...

02:02:42.213 --> 02:02:44.579
...and hands-on expertise.

02:02:45.650 --> 02:02:47.311
And that person...

02:02:48.219 --> 02:02:49.982
...is Stephanie Kaplan.

02:02:56.494 --> 02:02:58.724
Congratulations, Stephanie.

02:03:09.907 --> 02:03:12.842
I tell you something,
she's the greatest!

02:03:14.512 --> 02:03:16.173
Thank you.

02:03:16.681 --> 02:03:20.913
First, I'd like to take the opportunity
to thank the department heads:

02:03:21.252 --> 02:03:24.119
...Mary Anne Hunter
and Mark Lewyn here...

02:03:24.255 --> 02:03:27.247
...and Don Cherry, where are you?

02:03:28.125 --> 02:03:29.422
There he is.

02:03:29.627 --> 02:03:32.118
And particularly, Tom Sanders...

02:03:32.263 --> 02:03:35.926
...who epitomizes the
inventiveness of this division...

02:03:36.133 --> 02:03:37.691
...its past and its future.

02:03:38.536 --> 02:03:41.198
I'm counting on you to be
my right-hand.

02:03:42.540 --> 02:03:43.871
Thank you.

02:03:50.681 --> 02:03:53.912
We are heading
into a new millennium...

02:03:54.185 --> 02:03:55.243
...a new time.

02:03:56.020 --> 02:03:58.079
You a chemistry major, Spencer?

02:03:59.924 --> 02:04:01.084
Yeah, I am.

